{"questionId":"24173546","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Alvie wants to buy this car. On 1 January 2023, he invested <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>15</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math> in an account that earns <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math> annual interest compounded yearly. He makes no further deposits to, or withdrawals from, the account.</p>\n<p>Alvie wishes to buy this car for its value on 1 January 2028. In addition to the money in his account, he will need an extra <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mi>M</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>±</mo><mo>)</mo><mn>15000</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for use of a financial app in their technology with all entries correct.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>⇒</mo><mi>FV</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>±</mo><mo>)</mo><mn>17389</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>17389</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>subtracting their value from their answer to part (b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7572</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7570</mn></math> (dollars)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"24173546","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of M.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.4—Financial apps – compound int, annual depreciation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}